FBIS4-30607 "dreas124_a_94013" FBIS-EAS-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Hata Welcomes Agreement on Korean Summit Hata Welcomes Agreement on Korean Summit OW2806132994 Tokyo KYODO in English 1314 GMT 28 Jun 94 OW2806132994 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, June 28 KYODO -- Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata on Tuesday welcomed the agreement between North and South Korea to hold their first summit meeting next month, saying it is "good news." North and South Korean officials agreed earlier in the day to hold a meeting of their leaders in Pyongyang on July 25-27, followed by a second meeting at a later date, with the place still to be decided. The summit would also have a good effect on the relations between Japan and North Korea, Hata told reporters. On the prospects for Japanese economic and technological assistance to North Korea, Hata predicted smooth progress if the nuclear issue is settled in forthcoming high-level talks between the United States and North Korea.
